            "label": "Content",
            "value": "Miniature from a book of hours, depicting Christ for Pilate by the Master of Otto van Moerdrecht."
        },
        {
            "label": "Note",
            "value": [
                "'Christ for Pilate' was taken from the same codex as two other loose miniatures: 'Burial of Christ (kept in Cambridge, Fitzwilliam Museum under shelfmark 27-1991) and 'Virgin with Child' (kept in Cleveland Museum of Art, under shelfmark 12828/10). Similar style of miniatures in ms. The Hague, Royal Library, 135 K 45). Cf. Van Bergen 2007. - With a contemporary stamp of letter 'b' in the upper right corner (hidden in the decoration). - Early use as devotional image, in view of the passion prayer in French on the verso (c.1500?), written in an untrained hand.",
                "Origin and date: According to Van Bergen 2007.",
                "Description (Bouwman 2023): http://hdl.handle.net/1887.1/item:3619870",
                "Description (Gumbert 2009): http://hdl.handle.net/1887.1/item:3161419",
                "Also described by A.W. Byvanckgenootschap (database RKD, The Hague)."
            ]
